    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offering a superlative 1989 Porsche 911 Carrera 3.2, featuring the highly desirable G50 Getrag five-speed manual transaxle and Borg-Warner synchronizers. The numbers-matching air-cooled flat-six utilizes the Bosch Motronic DME system, delivering 217 hp with a linear torque curve and zero oil seepage from the crankcase or valve covers. The chassis remains factory-stiff, supported by a meticulously preserved torsion bar suspension and staggered Fuchs forged alloy wheels. Performance is further defined by its four-piston alloy calipers and ventilated rotors, showing no signs of thermal stress. This specimen boasts a flawless underbody with original cadmium plating intact and heat exchangers free of oxidation. A mechanically peerless example for the purist collector.",
